npmotornet - NumPy-based Motor Control Library
================================================

This is a derivative work based on MotorNet, converted from PyTorch to NumPy.

Original Work:
--------------
MotorNet: A Python toolbox for controlling differentiable biomechanical
effectors with artificial neural networks

Copyright (c) 2021-2024 Olivier Codol and contributors
Original repository: https://github.com/OlivierCodol/MotorNet
License: GNU General Public License v3.0

Derivative Work:
----------------
npmotornet - NumPy conversion
Copyright (c) 2025

Changes Made:
- Converted all PyTorch tensor operations to NumPy array operations
- Removed torch.nn.Module inheritance, replaced with plain Python classes
- Removed PyTorch Parameter wrappers
- Removed device management (GPU/CPU)
- Added fallback for gymnasium dependency
- All core functionality (skeleton, muscle, effector) converted to pure NumPy

